This is the folder for the Student Seaglider Center's Spring 2026 open ocean test mission.
Glider 174 was deployed off of Edmonds on May 18th 2026 and recovered on May 19th 2026. It completed 39 dives.

A CTD cast was completed during the deployment: RBR_05182026_Edmonds.xlsx .
The mission plan details all parts of deployment and recovery including personnel logistics, sensor details, tidal cycles, science questions, mission targets, boat traffic, mission preparation, budget, and safety procedures.

Inside this folder there is the clean data, raw files, meta data file, CTD cast, and mission plan.

The clean_data folder has csv and netCDF files that are corrected for the time offset and fewer renamed variables for simplicity in plotting. The raw data can still be found in raw_files > nc_files > the last file titled sg194_2026_04_17_Edmonds_Test_timeseries.nc
The clean_data folder also has csv and netCDF files for the depth averaged currents and finally a python script detailing the process for cleaning the data.

The raw_files folder has all the raw files that come off the basestation. These are sorted by file type. 

For any questions about this mission please contact the Mission PI, William Menapace (arnold64@uw.edu), or the Data associate, Sophie Monterola (somont@uw.edu).
